Steadfast

Passive Ability

When at 50% max HP or below, grants this Pokémon a shield and increases their movement speed by 20% for 5s (60s CD).

250% Atk + 50 x (Level - 1) + 50

Attack

Auto Attack

Becomes a boosted attack with increased range every third attack, damaging opposing Pokémon with a normal basic attack, then following up with a combo attack using a bone, damaging opposing Pokémon in the area a second time and throwing them for 0.5s.

100% Atk + 0 x (Level - 1) + 0

30% Atk + 0 x (Level - 1) + 0

Quick Attack

Move 1

6.00s Dash

The user dashes forward, damaging opposing Pokémon hit.

221% Atk + 11 x (Level - 1) + 240

Quick Attack Upgrade Choices

Extreme Speed

7.50s Dash

The user dashes forward, damaging opposing Pokémon and restoring the user's HP for each opposing Pokémon hit. The user can use a unique auto attack immediately at the end of the dash, dealing damage to opposing Pokémon in an area around them.

After learning this move, nearby opposing Pokémon have an Extreme Speed marker automatically applied to them. The first opposing Pokémon with a marker hit by Extreme Speed's dash will reset this move's cooldown and have their marker removed. There is a 10s cooldown before a target can have an Extreme Speed marker automatically applied to them again (apart from other moves).

208% Atk + 6 x (Level - 1) + 280

33.75% Atk + 1 x (Level - 1) + 42

75% Atk + 0 x (Level - 1) + 0

Increases the user's Attack by 7.5% for 2s when this move is used.

Power-Up Punch

7.00s Melee

The user receives 30% reduced damage and decreases their movement speed by 15% as they charge up power for up to 4s, reaching maximum charge after 1s; then dashes forward with a devastating punch when released, damaging the first opposing Pokémon hit, dealing additional missing HP damage to the target and shoving them for 0.5s. If this move hits, the user readies a boosted attack. This move's cooldown is reduced by 1s each time one of the user's moves lands a hit. If this move is canceled or not released after 4s, it goes on a 1.4s cooldown.

Against wild Pokémon: additional missing HP damage is capped at 1000.

209.16% Atk + 3 x (Level - 1) + 88

381.8% Atk + 5 x (Level - 1) + 161

Becomes unstoppable while charging this move.

Meteor Mash

Move 2

7.00s Melee

The user punches with the force of a meteor in the designated direction, damaging opposing Pokémon hit and shoving them.

167% Atk + 8 x (Level - 1) + 180

Meteor Mash Upgrade Choices

Bone Rush

10.00s Dash

The user rapidly strikes with a bone 3 times in the designated direction, damaging opposing Pokémon within melee range around Lucario, and in the area of the bone strikes in front; opposing Pokémon can be damaged twice per hit by being in the area directly in front of Lucario, where the bone strikes overlap with the attacks within melee range. The user then throws the bone flying to land a short distance away, shoving opposing Pokémon. This move can be used again to dash to the bone then catch it, damaging nearby opposing Pokémon when the bone is grabbed.

Landing one of the three initial strikes on opposing Pokémon applies an Extreme Speed marker to them.

41% Atk + 1 x (Level - 1) + 50

Catching the bone with the second use resets the cooldown of Extreme Speed or Power-Up Punch.

Close Combat

7.50s Melee

The user becomes unstoppable and rapidly punches in the designated direction, damaging opposing Pokémon in the area in front of them (up to 11 times), and restoring the user's HP each time this move hits.

The next auto attack within 5s after using this move gains increased range and causes the user to lunge at an opposing Pokémon with a kick.

50% Atk + 2 x (Level - 1) + 60

10% Atk + 0 x (Level - 1) + 20

Increases the damage of this move.

56% Atk + 2 x (Level - 1) + 69

Aura Cannon

Unite Move

112s 100000 Ranged

Unlocks at level 9

The user becomes unstoppable and channels aura into a huge sphere, then launches the sphere in the designated direction, dealing damage to opposing Pokémon in its path. The aura sphere picks up speed as it travels; at close range, a target can be hit up to 4 times, while at max speed a target will only be hit once.

If the user learned Extreme Speed, targets hit by this Unite Move have an Extreme Speed marker applied to them. If the user learned Power-Up Punch, this Unite Move strengthens the damage of the next attack of Power-Up Punch by roughly 20% and the shove duration to 1s.

174% Atk + 4 x (Level - 1) + 210

Unite Buffs (6s duration):

30% Movement Speed, 30% CDR, 20% Max HP Shield
